cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.CC. 

This paper deals with computational geometry, specifically the problem of covering polygons with convex polygons. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and data structures, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as another likely sub-category. The problem of covering polygons by convex polygons can also be formulated as an optimization problem, which could place it in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves game theory, which could place it in cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). Finally, the paper involves computational complexity, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
